ines as a deathtrap for investors buffett had made an investment in us airways in  which although he sold for a profit almost lost berkshire a substantial sum of money as of  berkshire is currently the largest shareholder in united airlines and delta air lines and a top  shareholder in southwest airlines and american airlines buffett himself has described this as a call on the industry rather than a choice in an individual company american airlines ceo doug parker is said to have won over ted weschler in arguing that the airline industry had consolidated sufficiently and rationalised supply such that longer term profitability could be achieved in an industry that has historically been loss making in aggregate prior investmentsedit berkshire previously held a considerable stake in tesco plc the uk grocery retailer berkshire made its first investment in tesco in  and in  raised this stake to over  of the company with a cost for the investment of  billion buffett sold around  of this stake in  when he “soured somewhat on the company’s thenmanagement” realising a profit of  million as tescos problems mounted through  berkshire sold all the remaining shares with buffett saying to shareholders that the delay in selling shares was costly berkshire made an aftertax loss of  million on the tesco investment subsidiaries and equity holdingsedit main article list of assets owned by berkshire hathaway assetsedit main article list of assets owned by berkshire hathaway see alsoedit nebraska portal companies portal list of berkshire hathaway publications notesedit  a b c d e f berkshire hathaway inc  annual report form k xbrl united states securities and exchange commission february     berkshire hathaway portfolio tracker cnbc retrieved    warren buffett  annual report pdf p  retrieved  may    top  biggest conglomerates in the world based by revenue therichest  retrieved    the worlds biggest public companies forbescom retrieved may     berkshire hathaway forbes retrieved june    